WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.352 --> 00:00:03.693
Supply chain management or SCM,

2
00:00:03.693 --> 00:00:06.072
is the seamless management and integration

3
00:00:06.072 --> 00:00:09.336
of the flow of material or service information

4
00:00:09.336 --> 00:00:12.088
and finances across the entire supply chain

5
00:00:12.088 --> 00:00:14.243
and among all supply chain partners

6
00:00:14.243 --> 00:00:16.035
throughout the life cycle.

7
00:00:16.035 --> 00:00:18.245
It is comprised of the decisions a business

8
00:00:18.245 --> 00:00:19.765
makes about it's supply chain

9
00:00:19.765 --> 00:00:21.226
and to the active management

10
00:00:21.226 --> 00:00:23.797
of the flow of goods and services.

11
00:00:23.797 --> 00:00:26.655
Supply chain leaders must make ongoing decisions

12
00:00:26.655 --> 00:00:30.270
that weigh explicit trade-offs regarding resource allocation

13
00:00:30.270 --> 00:00:33.247
and priorities, setting supply chain targets

14
00:00:33.247 --> 00:00:37.493
and driving changes to behavior and updates to policy.

15
00:00:37.493 --> 00:00:40.723
Effectively managing a supply chain calls for open lines

16
00:00:40.723 --> 00:00:43.043
of communication between all actors

17
00:00:43.043 --> 00:00:46.965
along with formalized roles and responsibilities.

18
00:00:46.965 --> 00:00:49.658
The major activities under supply chain management

19
00:00:49.658 --> 00:00:52.730
include planning and scheduling,

20
00:00:52.730 --> 00:00:55.245
purchasing, inventory control,

21
00:00:55.245 --> 00:00:58.927
storage, distribution, and excessing.

22
00:00:58.927 --> 00:01:02.735
As a result of having proper storage levels of supplies,

23
00:01:02.735 --> 00:01:06.223
it is important to work with your customers (clinicians)

24
00:01:06.223 --> 00:01:09.423
to set appropriate and real usage levels.

25
00:01:09.423 --> 00:01:11.429
It is also important to communicate

26
00:01:11.429 --> 00:01:13.210
with your Prime Vendor to ensure

27
00:01:13.210 --> 00:01:14.789
the supplies can be delivered

28
00:01:14.789 --> 00:01:17.402
to the facility in a timely manner.

29
00:01:17.402 --> 00:01:19.512
Supply chain management works best

30
00:01:19.512 --> 00:01:22.907
when what is needed is delivered and used by the customer.

